3. d4
{ That was our plan: build a perfect pawn center. Now we get to the first crucial moment. After  3.d4  , Black's best reply is rarely played. It is  3...d5!  , when  4.exd5  Qxd5  transposes to a position we examine via @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp1ppppp/8/2p5/4P3/2P5/PP1P1PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2...d5  3.exd5  Qxd5  4.d4  Nc6  , a viable main line for Black.   In practice, however, Black usually trades on d4, which is less precise. We'll look at this move, but also at  3...e6?  , which is a mistake. }
