5... c6
{ Black wants to lend some additional support to the d-pawn. You'll also meet @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/8/3p4/2PP4/8/PP3PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq c3 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4...c6  when  5.Nc3  Nf6  leads to the position we have on the board. Our plan is easy: we continue our standard setup  of Nf3, Bd3, and O-O. }
